Police officers in Thika are investigating an incident in which a 46-year-old man is said to have died in his car while reportedly having sex with his 25-year-old girlfriend. According to a police report seen by Citizen Digital, a sudden death report was filed at the Thika Police station at around midnight on Sunday. “It was reported by PC Anne Kemunto that today at about 0000 hours, she was informed by the security guard that one male adult had died outside his car,” the report says. The police report says that the OCS Thika Police station and the DCI team rushed to the scene where they they discovered one John Gicheru lying outside his car. His lover Apofia Oyego who claims to have dated the deceased the past one year was seated beside his body. The police recovered some Ksh.850, an I-phone 6 mobile phone, car key, handkerchief and a Subaru motor vehicle of registration KCJ 530C. Also Read: “It was also noted that the deceased’s private parts were swollen,”  the report says. The body of the decreased was moved to the General Kago Funeral Home pending an autopsy. The 25-year-old woman is currently in custody as probe into the death continues. Video Of The Day: KEMRI scientists examine safety of anti-malarial drugs in first trimester of pregnancy